23:43.910 --> 24:05.867
science, those that were interested in eggs as a 
science project. And so we've discontinued

24:05.847 --> 24:13.819
because we've gone just about as far as we can on 
this. We're just going to have to learn more

24:13.939 --> 24:17.905
biology before we can take them all the way 
through. But there's some hope that you might be

24:18.426 --> 24:20.629
able to do that someday. Oh, I don't think in a doubt 
that we'll be able to do it someday. I won't, but I

24:23.874 --> 24:27.719
won't live that long, but somebody will. Yes, 
indeed.

24:31.565 --> 24:32.867
Then we... We did some work on clay feeding, 
bentonite and clay work, and we have gotten some

24:33.337 --> 24:46.229
definite responses from feeding of clay to these 
laying hens. There's also been some reports since

24:46.950 --> 24:54.777
our first paper, there's been some reports from 
other areas for feeding it to broilers. How they

24:56.158 --> 25:00.542
get any additional response from the feed because 
it includes a little clay, I do not know. And I will

25:06.473 --> 25:17.353
never have time to really determine one of the 
suspicions I have as to why. I have a feeling that

25:17.774 --> 25:23.965
probably these clays are extremely fine 
particles, most of the clays. And I have a feeling

25:23.945 --> 25:40.682
that the nutrients coat these clay particles and 
that gives a greater surface exposure to the villi

25:23.945 --> 25:40.682
on the lining of the digestive tract so that the 
absorption rate is perhaps higher. I don't know

25:40.902 --> 25:46.427
that this is it, but I'd like to be able to test it. 
And I got far enough to get a company that said they

25:46.447 --> 25:53.074
would make me clays of different glands. granular 
sizes so I could do it. I may get back to it in my

25:57.065 --> 26:07.131
retirement days and further test it, but that's as 
far as we've gone on that. And then there's two

26:07.820 --> 26:17.374
other areas that I'd definitely like to mention 
that I think we've made some fairly original

26:07.820 --> 26:17.374
contributions. One is that quite a number of years 
ago, we fed to these laying hens, we fed... eggs. We

26:30.951 --> 26:36.383
simply took the feed and then put in the equivalent 
of one egg per man per day. Two eggs, three eggs,

26:36.583 --> 26:41.192
four eggs, seven eggs, and ten eggs per man per day. 
And fed these hens for a full year. on this to

26:45.822 --> 26:54.172
determine about this cholesterol thing that we 
hear so much about, particularly in the medical

26:45.822 --> 26:54.172
profession. Well, we actually found that the 
higher the level of eggs we included, the better

26:54.192 --> 27:03.382
the performance of the birds and the lower the 
mortality.

27:08.148 --> 27:12.673
I don't think there's any doubt that this is 
significant.

27:15.269 --> 27:23.839
And then the... Can

27:15.269 --> 27:23.839
we step back to that a minute? You say one egg per man 
per day. Now, do you mean per chicken? Yeah. In

27:30.247 --> 27:41.901
other words, that hen consumed in her diet, she 
consumed the amount of egg that a man would

27:30.247 --> 27:41.901
consume...

27:42.607 --> 27:43.329
in a day. I wanted to feed these hens at different 
levels of consumption, of egg consumption. So I

27:51.147 --> 27:54.315
fed them on equivalent to a man basis, you see. In 
other words, this group of hens got no eggs added.

27:59.093 --> 28:10.434
This one got the equivalent eggs added, 
equivalent to a man, an average man and woman, and

27:59.093 --> 28:10.434
the average size, consuming one egg per man per 
day. And then two and so on, up to ten eggs per man,

28:10.995 --> 28:22.637
equivalent of a man would be eating ten eggs if he 
had got as much eggs as his hen was getting, don't

28:10.995 --> 28:22.637
you see? So you would adjust for the body weight of 
the chicken. A chicken of a certain size would get a

28:29.357 --> 28:32.182
certain portion of an egg. Yes, yeah. And in other 
words, the ratio was here so we could check to see

28:34.306 --> 28:42.901
what effect these eggs had, the cholesterol in the 
eggs. There were whole eggs given to these birds.

28:51.575 --> 29:18.088
And

28:51.575 --> 29:18.088
we also did some work and were asked to report it at 
several seminars on the relation of calcium

29:19.739 --> 29:32.038
source and the particle size of the calcium, its 
