Oh, we have also did quite an extensive amount of 
work feeding of dwarf or many layers, the dwarf

30:08.693 --> 30:14.442
birds versus normal birds. And we have showed that 
to get optimum performance from the dwarf birds,

30:15.104 --> 30:23.998
you have to feed a higher density diet. Their 
capacity is lower, and thus you have to increase

30:24.539 --> 30:34.195
the concentration of the nutrients in the diet 
that they get. And we were early in doing that.

